# Contributing

Thanks for considering a contribution. The short version:

1. **Read [`AGENTS.md`](./AGENTS.md).** It's the canonical style and testing
   guide. `CLAUDE.md` is a symlink to it.
2. **Prerequisites**: Python {{ python_version }}+, [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/),
   [just](https://github.com/casey/just).
3. **Fork, branch, open a PR.** CI must pass.

## Workflow

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/{{ package_name }}
cd {{ package_name }}
just install     # uv sync + pre-commit install
just all         # format + lint + test
```

## Opening a PR

- Fill out the PR template — especially the "AI-generated code reviewed
  line-by-line" checkbox.
- Keep PRs focused. One concern per PR.
- The PR title will appear in the release changelog — make it read well.

## Reporting bugs

Open an issue with a minimal reproducer. If the bug involves an external API,
include the VCR cassette or the relevant request/response.
